formation and implementation, the role of men in women's economic lives, low-income women's beliefs and aspirations, and the possibilities for women cooperatively working to change the welfare system. Indeed, Kingfisher demonstrates that women who are often viewed as victims without control actively work within the confines of the system to exert their autonomy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aAid to families with dependent children programsxUnited States. 0aAid to families with dependent children programszUnited States. 0aAide sociale aux familles avec enfants à chargevÉtats-Unis. 0aAide sociale aux familles avec enfants à chargexÉtats-Unis. 0aAide socialevBénéficiairesvÉtats-Unis. 0aAide socialevÉtats-Unis. 0aAide socialexBénéficiairesxÉtats-Unis. 0aAide socialexÉtats-Unis. 0aDéfense des droits économiques et sociauxvÉtats-Unis. 0aDéfense des droits économiques et sociauxxÉtats-UnisxUnited StatesxMichigan. 0aFemmes pauvresvÉtats-Unis. 0aFemmes pauvresxÉtats-Unis. 0aHuman services personnelxUnited States. 0aHuman services personnelzUnited States. 0aPolitical sciencevPublic PolicyvGeneral. 0aPoor womenxUnited States. 0aPoor womenzUnited States. 0aPublic welfarexUnited States. 0aPublic welfarezUnited States. 0aServices sociauxvPersonnelvÉtats-Unis. 0aServices sociauxxPersonnelxÉtats-Unis. 0aWelfare recipientsxUnited States. 0aWelfare recipientszUnited States. 0aWelfare rights movementxUnited States. 0aWelfare rights movementzUnited States. 4aGender Studies. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPublic Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Pa